import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import ImageGrid

# c12_path = "./exp/num_scales-1000/workdir/eval_folder/ode_ckpt_12/samples_0.npz"
# c32_path = "./exp/num_scales-1000/workdir/eval_folder/pc_ckpt_32/samples_0.npz"
# c56_path = "./exp/num_scales-1000/workdir/eval_folder/pc_ckpt_56/samples_0.npz"
c16_13M = "./exp/13M/workdir/eval_folder/ckpt_16/samples_0.npz"

sample_file = np.load(c16_13M)
samples = sample_file['samples']

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(100,100))
grid = ImageGrid(fig, 111,  # similar to subplot(111)
                 nrows_ncols=(10, 10),  # creates 2x2 grid of axes
                 axes_pad=0.1,  # pad between axes in inch.
                 )

for ax, im in zip(grid, samples[:100]):
    ax.axis('off')
    ax.imshow(im)

plt.show()
